headline: Rosalind Franklin University Helix 51 Company UP Oncolytics Secures Wisconsin Economic Development Matching Grant to Advance Oncolytic Virus Therapy for Brain Cancer
summary: UP Oncolytics, a neuro-oncology biotechnology company based in Milwaukee and a spin-out of the Advocate Aurora Research Institute, has received a $75,000 matching grant from the Wisconsin Economic Development Corporation (WEDC) in partnership with the University of Wisconsin. The grant supplements the company's $500,000 SBIR Phase I Fast Track award from the National Institutes of Health (NIH), received last year.
